main event: A civilian reported a UFO sighting in Aiken, South Carolina, on March 25, 1968, observing a bright object with changing colors over a span of 2 minutes.
interesting points: The observer mentioned the object emitted bright lights that changed colors and seemed to be accelerating,The report indicated a possibility of misidentification due to a DC-9 jet flight in the vicinity at the time,The observer did not provide enough descriptive data about the object's characteristics,The sighting occurred at approximately 6:50 p.m.,The investigation concluded insufficient data for evaluation and deemed the sighting not valid.
witness description: A civilian observer refused to provide further information but claimed to have seen the object.
